Package: teachrag
Title: Teaching Materials RAG with Ollama and Claude
Version: 0.1.0
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Authors@R: person("Felix", "Lennert", email = "felix@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) for course materials. Parses teaching
  materials (slides, scripts, syllabus), builds a DuckDB-backed ragnar store with
  embeddings, and provides single-turn or multi-turn Q&A via Ollama (local) or
  Claude (API). Includes a Shiny app for interactive use.
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Suggests:
  testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Imports:
  digest (>= 0.6.0),
  dplyr (>= 1.2.0),
  ellmer,
  fs,
  ollamar,
  purrr,
  ragnar,
  readr,
  shiny,
  stringr,
  tibble,
  tidyr
